arriage  career  death  references  external links early lifeedit mark reynolds hughes was born to father stuard hartman not stuart per birth certificate and mother jo ann hughes his parents divorced in  when mark was  and his mother retained custody of mark at this point the family survived on welfare payments with hughes mother suffering from “emotional problems” she battled obesity and tension via amphetamines and sleeping pills in the ninth grade hughes dropped out of school and began using drugs himself “i was a little delinquent” he says “i got in trouble with the law” at  he was sent to cedu high school a private residential school for troubled youngsters in running springs ca whose origins went back to a cult founded in  part of hughes cedu rehab required him to raise money by selling raffle tickets hughes became the school’s best salesman “the approval there was based on how much funds you raised” hughes told people magazine in  “there was a lot of pressure and i wanted to be the best right away” hughes was  years old and still working for cedu when his mother died in her apartment of a accidental drug overdose on april   according to the autopsy report several empty vials of prescription drugs were found beside her bed and her doctor told the coroner she was known to overingest her prescription drugs toxicological tests showed potentially lethal levels of the painkiller darvon in her system preherbalife career and first marriageedit in  the yearold hughes began selling diet products for seyforth laboratories a multilevel marketer becoming one of its top  earners after seyforth collapsed in  hughes then sold exercise equipment and weightcontrol products for a company called golden youth also a directsales outfit it was while working for golden youth in  that hughes met kathryn whiting the first of four beauty pageant winners he would marry on the beach whiting a former miss santa monica was then a year old college student pursing a degree in medical science when golden youth also went out of business hughes decided to start his own operation careeredit in february  aged  hughes founded los angelesbased herbalife international it has since become one of the worlds largest distributors of herbal products through multilevel marketing with sales of about  billion in  and  million independent distributors now in  countries and achieving record retail sales of  billion in  according to company statements in the mids hughes was sued by the food and drug administration the california attorney generals office and the state department of health over what they said were false health claims about herbalife products and the various schemes used to market them health agencies accused the company of violating labeling standards and using improper sales practices regulators contended that the company was making medicinal claims medicines are regulated by the fda while nutritional supplements are not some health experts doubted the efficacy of herbalife products saying that in some instances they relied too heavily on laxatives and caffeine in march  the california attorney general and the state department of health services charged him and herbalife with making untrue or misleading product claims—primarily involving the caffeine content of some herbalife products—and operating an endless chain marketing scheme prompted by complaints alleging that herbalife product users had suffered illness and death a us senate subcommittee called hughes before a hearing in may referring to a panel of nutrition experts who had criticized herbalife in testimony the previous day he asked the senators if theyre such experts in weight loss why were they so fat during the hearing hughes acknowledged that his own formal education stopped at the th grade when asked during the hearing how he could be qualified to challenge leading medical experts hughes responded i defy anybody to be able to produce results as this company has hughes reached settlements with the regulatory agencies in  to settle his problems with the state hughes agreed to pay  at the time the california attorney general john van de kamp was quoted in the wall street journal as saying it was the largest settlement ever attained from a health products company in december  hughes and his third wife suzan hughes had a son alexander reynolds alex hughes deathedit on the night of saturday may   hughes celebrated the th birthday of his maternal grandmother hazel known as mimi it was a private gathering with a few family members joining him at his mansion in malibu for the evening out of the public limelight hughes drank white wine smoked a cigar and played his drum set hughes was trying to buy up all outstanding shares of herbalife and take the company private once more the stress and long hours had taken a toll on his health he was recovering from a recurrence of pneumonia the treatment involved corticosteroids which made sleeping difficult his physician prescribed the drug doxepin a tricyclic antidepressant for the insomnia and according to security guards at  century park east he was found dead in his office with a pile of cocaine in front of him on may   authorities said that mark hughes died of an accidental overdose after mixing alcohol with a toxic level of antidepressants scott carrier of the los angeles county coroners office said final autopsy results found that hughes  had ingested a toxic combination of alcohol and doxepin an antidepressant he was taking to help him sleep his bloodalcohol level was measured at  hughes then yearold son alexander alex hughes was named sole beneficiary of his fathers estate estimated to be worth  million hughess will stipulated that until alex turns  the bulk of his inheritance would be held in a trust managed by hughes father jack reynolds attorney conrad klein and herbalife executive christopher pair in  the los angeles superior court ruled to remove reynolds from supervising a  million custodianship after finding that he violated multiple probate laws by ceding control to klein and commingling alexs personal assets with partnership accounts reynolds was suspended but remained one of three trustees until  when a judge in a separate lawsuit ordered the removal of all three for breaching the terms of the trust by mismanaging the funds referencesedit  binge led ot death of herbalife founder new york times  june  retrieved  june    a b c d e despite critics and lawsuits herbalife has made mark hughes wealthy if not healthy retrieved    a b safety methods questioned  herbalife weighty profits and government probes retrieved   cite error invalid ref tag name latimescom defined multiple times with different content see the help page  the cult that spawned the toughlove teen industry mother jones retrieved    synanon cedu  brown schools medical whistleblower medicalwhistleblowernetworkjigsycom retrieved    the history of synanon and charles dederich wwwpaulmorantzcom retrieved    a b c d e f shuit douglas p may   mark hughes founder of herbalife dies at  los angeles times retrieved november     a b c copage eric v may   mark r hughes  founded nutrition supplement concern the new york times retrieved november     herbalife’s mark hughes pdf retrieved    copage eric v  mark r hughes  founded nutrition supplement concern the new york times issn  retrieved    herbalife and mark hughes  a success story explosivemlmcom retrieved    jackson robert l may   testifies at stormy senate hearing herbalife president calls diet powders pills safe los angeles times retrieved november     heller matthew february   death and denial at herbalife los angeles times p  retrieved november     autopsy on herbalife founder finds death caused by accidental overdose cnn june   archived from the original on november     townsend mark september   legal battle rages around americas richest teenager the observer the guardian retrieved november     cumings stephanie september   herbalife heir cant object to settl