aine in front of him on may   authorities said that mark hughes died of an accidental overdose after mixing alcohol with a toxic level of antidepressants scott carrier of the los angeles county coroners office said final autopsy results found that hughes  had ingested a toxic combination of alcohol and doxepin an antidepressant he was taking to help him sleep his bloodalcohol level was measured at  hughes then yearold son alexander alex hughes was named sole beneficiary of his fathers estate estimated to be worth  million hughess will stipulated that until alex turns  the bulk of his inheritance would be held in a trust managed by hughes father jack reynolds attorney conrad klein and herbalife executive christopher pair in  the los angeles superior court ruled to remove reynolds from supervising a  million custodianship after finding that he violated multiple probate laws by ceding control to klein and commingling alexs personal assets with partnership accounts reynolds was suspended but remained one of three trustees until  when a judge in a separate lawsuit ordered the removal of all three for breaching the terms of the trust by mismanaging the funds referencesedit  binge led ot death of herbalife founder new york times  june  retrieved  june    a b c d e despite critics and lawsuits herbalife has made mark hughes wealthy if not healthy retrieved    a b safety methods questioned  herbalife weighty profits and government probes retrieved   cite error invalid ref tag name latimescom defined multiple times with different content see the help page  the cult that spawned the toughlove teen industry mother jones retrieved    synanon cedu  brown schools medical whistleblower medicalwhistleblowernetworkjigsycom retrieved    the history of synanon and charles dederich wwwpaulmorantzcom retrieved    a b c d e f shuit douglas p may   mark hughes founder of herbalife dies at  los angeles times retrieved november     a b c copage eric v may   mark r hughes  founded nutrition s